			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2011</a> paper:</span><br><i>Cloning in DSLs: Experiments with OCL</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/RobertTairas.html">Robert Tairas</a>, <a href="../profile/JordiCabot.html">Jordi Cabot</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-28830-2_4">10.1007/978-3-642-28830-2_4</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t2b.html"><span class="tagM">T2B: Evolution</span></a><ul><li> The paper studies clone detection/handling in DSL artifacts as a maintenance and quality concern.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3c.html"><span class="tagL">T3C: DSLs</span></a><ul><li> The problem and evaluation are explicitly situated in the context of DSLs and their models.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5e.html"><span class="tagL">T5E: Empirical Evaluation</span></a><ul><li> The contribution is validated through experiments (an empirical study) using OCL-based techniques.
</li></ul></li></ul>
